excerpt: Lovina Beach is a resort area on the north coast of Bali, Indonesia. It’s known for its black sand beaches, coral reefs and dolphins. From the village of Temoekoes, a trail leads to Singsing Waterfall and a Dutch war monument. The Banjar Hot Springs have warm water pools and tropical gardens. The Brahmavihara-Arama Buddhist monastery is home to a miniature replica of the huge Javanese archaeological site Borobudur.
detail_description: Lovina Beach, located on the northern coast of Bali, Indonesia, is a popular resort area known for its stunning black sand beaches, vibrant coral reefs, and playful dolphins. Visitors can explore the nearby village of Temoekoes to discover the trail leading to Singsing Waterfall and a Dutch war monument. The Banjar Hot Springs offer warm water pools nestled within tropical gardens while the Brahmavihara-Arama Buddhist monastery houses a miniature replica of Borobudur.
name: Lovina Beach
address: Anturan, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali, Indonesia

excerpt: Singaraja is a port town in northern Bali, Indonesia. It's known for Dutch colonial–era warehouses on its waterfront. Gedong Kirtya Library houses ancient palm-leaf manuscripts (lontar). Museum Buleleng displays stone coffins and ceremonial masks. Pictures of Buleleng kings adorn the 1600s royal palace Puri Agung. Pura Jagatnatha temple has carvings of Hindu gods. South, Gitgit Waterfall is set amid tropical forest.
detail_description: Singaraja, a charming port town in northern Bali, Indonesia, is steeped in history and culture. The Dutch colonial–era warehouses along the waterfront offer a glimpse into its past. Visitors can explore ancient palm-leaf manuscripts at Gedong Kirtya Library and view stone coffins and ceremonial masks at Museum Buleleng.
name: Singaraja
address: Banyuasri, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali, Indonesia

detail_description: Museum Buleleng, located in Singaraja, offers a glimpse into the history of the area and its surroundings. The museum is home to Gedong Kertya, a library housing lontar books that delve into Balinese history, religion, and literature. These traditional books are crafted from palm leaves using intricate carving techniques. While it's a small museum that can be explored in under 30 minutes, it provides an insightful look into the regency of Buleleng.
name: Museum Buleleng (ᬫᬸᬲᬶᬬᬸᬫ᭄ ᬩᬸᬮᬾᬮᬾᬂ᭟ )
address: Jl. Veteran No.23, Paket Agung, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81118, Indonesia

detail_description: Klenteng Ling Gwan Kiong is a well-preserved Chinese temple located in Singaraja, North Bali. It was established in 1873 and offers a serene atmosphere without crowds or entrance fees. The temple overlooks the former seaport complex and is situated near Pura Segara temple. Visitors can easily access the location from the highway and enjoy its cleanliness and sacred ambiance.
name: Klenteng Ling Gwan Kiong
address: Jl. Erlangga No.65, Kp. Bugis, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81114, Indonesia

excerpt: Cement stairs lead the way up to 4 waterfalls where tourists can slide down & swim in natural pools.
detail_description: Aling-Aling Waterfall, located in the village of Sambangan, Bali, is a serene and less crowded alternative to other popular waterfalls on the island. The journey to the waterfall offers stunning views of lush greenery and rice terraces as visitors descend a few hundred steps to reach it.
name: Aling-Aling Waterfall
address: Sambangan, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia

excerpt: Library containing many manuscripts & historic documents from the Dutch-colonial period.
detail_description: Gedong Kirtya is a small museum located in Bali, housing a collection of ancient manuscripts and historic documents from the Dutch-colonial period. The library was founded by the Dutch in front of the Puri Agung grounds and has been restored due to previous neglect. Visitors are welcome to explore this repository of Lontar manuscripts, gaining insight into Bali's rich literary heritage.
name: Gedong Kirtya
address: Jl. Veteran No.20, Paket Agung, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81118, Indonesia

name: Pasar Anyar Singaraja
address: Jl. Durian, Kampung Kajanan, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81114, Indonesia

excerpt: Lush foliage frames this tall waterfall with natural swimming pools, accessible by walking trail.
detail_description: Nestled in the lush greenery of Singaraja, North Bali, Gitgit Waterfall is a popular attraction known for its accessibility and natural beauty. The 35-meter-tall waterfall is easily reached by road and offers a scenic walking trail with refreshment stops and arts and crafts shops along the way. Visitors can enjoy the sight of wild monkeys amidst the trees while taking a refreshing dip in the natural swimming pools at the base of the waterfall.
name: Gitgit Waterfall
address: Jl. Raya Bedugul - Singaraja, Gitgit, Sukasada, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81161, Indonesia

excerpt: Hot springs complex surrounded by tropical gardens offering pools & showers, plus an eatery & a spa.
detail_description: Nestled in the lush Balinese jungle, Banjar Hot Spring is a natural hot springs complex surrounded by tropical gardens. The pools and showers offer a therapeutic experience, with the large upper pool gushing from stone Naga into lower pools. Located near Lake Batur, this serene spot is said to alleviate stress and heal various ailments. Visitors can also enjoy the nearby Buddhist monastery and take in panoramic views of the area.
name: Banjar Hot Spring
address: Jalan Banjar, Banjar, Kec. Banjar, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81152, Indonesia

detail_description: Nestled in the serene highlands of Bali, the Handara Iconic Gate is a breathtaking entrance that leads to a world of tranquility and natural beauty. This traditional Balinese gate showcases meticulous craftsmanship with its split design, offering a surreal and picture-perfect moment surrounded by lush landscapes. Reflecting Bali's rich heritage, the gate's architecture is a masterpiece of symmetry and cultural significance.
name: Handara Iconic Gate
address: Jl. Bali Handara Kosaido Golf Course, Pancasari, Sukasada, Buleleng Regency, Bali 82191, Indonesia

detail_description: Air Sanih Natural Spring is a charming village swimming pool with a rustic feel. The natural spring water pools are clear and cool, offering a rejuvenating swim in a tranquil setting surrounded by lush greenery and scenic views of the sea. While not luxurious, it's an ideal place to spend a few hours unwinding. Visitors can bring their own food and drinks or purchase some from small stores inside. The area offers minimal shade but has pagoda-type areas and trees for relief from the sun.
name: Air sanih natural spring
address: W6C8+VR3, Jl. Singaraja-Amlapura, Bukti, Kec. Kubutambahan, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81172, Indonesia

excerpt: Cement stairs lead the way up to 4 waterfalls where tourists can slide down & swim in natural pools.
detail_description: The Aling-Aling Waterfall is a popular tourist destination with cement steps leading to four cascades, where visitors can enjoy sliding and swimming in natural pools. This remote waterfall group is situated in a serene environment with limited crowds. It is recommended to hire a guide like Gordon who can assist and entertain you during your exploration. While walking around, it's advised to remove your shoes for better comfort instead of wearing tevas or water shoes.
name: Aling-Aling Waterfall
address: Sambangan, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia

detail_description: Pura Dalem Jagaraga Temple in Bali, Indonesia, stands as a symbol of Balinese resistance against colonial forces. The temple is adorned with unique reliefs and holds historical significance dating back to the war era. Visitors are welcomed by friendly locals who share the temple's rich history, including its destruction and subsequent reconstruction. The well-maintained gardens provide a peaceful setting for prayer and reflection, making it a serene and historically significant destination for travelers seeking to immerse themselves in Balinese culture.
name: Pura Dalem Jagaraga Temple
address: Jagaraga, Sawan, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81171, Indonesia

detail_description: Lemukih Waterfalls, located in Lemukih Village, Sawan District, Buleleng Regency, Bali Province, is a popular tourist destination known for its unique feature of having three waterfalls in one location. Despite being only 4 meters high, the waterfall boasts a large pool suitable for swimming. Visitors recommend hiring a local guide who can provide valuable insights into the surrounding flora and fauna during the trek to the falls.
name: Lemukih Waterfalls
address: dinas buah banjah, Lemukih banjar, Kec. Sawan, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81171, Indonesia

detail_description: PELABUHAN TUA BULELENG, located in Singaraja, is a popular spot to catch breathtaking sunsets. This area was once a bustling dock and now features four charming restaurants situated on a pier. Visitors can enjoy delicious food, stunning views, and reasonable prices while sipping on the local favorite, Bir Bintang. Although the ambiance is beautiful during the day, some suggest that brighter lighting would enhance the experience for nighttime photography.
name: PELABUHAN TUA BULELENG
address: V3WQ+JHH, Kp. Bugis, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81114, Indonesia

excerpt: Library containing many manuscripts & historic documents from the Dutch-colonial period.
detail_description: The Gedong Kirtya library houses a vast collection of manuscripts and historic documents from the Dutch-colonial period in Indonesia. It is important to note that this location is correct, as there is another Museum Gedong Kirtya nearby with an incorrect address. The knowledgeable staff at the library provide valuable information about ancient Balinese writing and the intricate process of creating "Lontar" books. Visitors are required to pay a fee of 5000 Rp for entry.
name: Gedong Kirtya
address: Jl. Veteran No.20, Paket Agung, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81118, Indonesia

detail_description: Bali Jungle Trekking Sambangan Waterfall Point offers an unforgettable experience with the friendly and skilled guide, Ketut. Visitors can enjoy jumping off 5, 10, and 15-meter cliffs into the crystal-clear water and floating down the waterfall. Hiring a guide is recommended as they provide valuable knowledge about the local ecology. Families with kids can have a fantastic time on the medium trek, which includes hiking, swimming in mountain lakes, sliding down waterfalls, and jumping off cliffs.
name: Bali Jungle Trekking Sambangan Waterfall Point
address: Banjar, Sambangan, Sukasada, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81161, Indonesia

excerpt: Jungle waterfall popular for jumping into its pool & whizzing down a natural rock slide.
detail_description: Nestled in the lush jungle of Sambangan Village, Sukasada District, Bali Province, Kroya Waterfall is a hidden gem waiting to be explored. Unlike its more popular counterparts, this waterfall offers a serene and uncrowded atmosphere for visitors to enjoy. The main highlight of Kroya Waterfall is its stunning blue lagoons that provide ample opportunities for swimming and relaxation.
name: Kroya Waterfall
address: Sambangan, Sukasada, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81161, Indonesia

excerpt: A jungle hike including stairs leads to this scenic waterfall with a secluded feel.
detail_description: Wanagiri Pucak Manik Waterfall is a hidden gem nestled in the lush jungle of Bali. The access to this scenic waterfall is well-maintained, with stairs leading down the hill. Although the track can be challenging, the breathtaking and pristine views make it worth the effort. With its secluded feel and lesser-known status, Wanagiri Pucak Manik Waterfall offers a serene escape from the crowds, allowing visitors to enjoy its beauty in tranquility.
name: Wanagiri Pucak Manik Waterfall
address: depan wisata wanagiri hidden hill, Jalan Raya Wanagiri-Munduk, Dusun Asah Panji, Wanagiri, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia

detail_description: Tugu Singa Ambara Raja is a significant monument in the city of Buleleng, commemorating the power of Ki Gusti Ngurah Panji Sakti, a revered leader from the 1660s. The statue features a winged lion holding a shepherd's crook, symbolizing strength and bravery. Situated at a T-junction in Singaraja's city center, it stands on a lotus-shaped pillar.
name: Tugu Singa Ambara Raja
address: Jl. Ngurah Rai, Banjar Paketan, Paket Agung, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81118, Indonesia

name: Monumen Patung I Gusti Ngurahrai
address: Jl. Gajah Mada No.1a, Kendran, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81112, Indonesia
